Maintainer:
    Adrian Serohijos <adrian.serohijos@umontreal.ca>
Description:We developed Doblin, an R suite for quantifying dominant clonal lineages from DNA barcoding time-series data. This package performs clustering of barcode lineage time-series, leveraging the idea that similarities in lineage trajectories reflect comparable relative fitness values. Our approach also identifies persistent clonal lineages in the population. Input data can also be time-series of mutants from selection experiments of mutational libraries or variants from CRISPR/Cas screens.
